If you find any spelling or grammar errors, be sure to berate me after fixing them.

For anything else, just let me know here and I'll take it into consideration.

And before anyone else brings it up, what exactly the different classes of amnesiac correspond to is disputed and ultimately not officially established, so I tried to leave it ambiguous.

On the ordering of the addenda: The first one happened before the second one chronologically, so that's why I put the breach one before the AMN-868 one. Addendum 868-1 does reference AMN-868, but I imagine that that would be because it was edited (along with the containment procedures) after AMN-868 was created.

On the redaction of the cleanup costs: I have no idea what covering up a military/paramilitary/whoknowswhat operation would cost, so there's a 90% chance that I would be wrong if I put something there. Plus, I imagine the Foundation would want to redact exactly how much money they have on hand for this sort of thing.

On the Euclid classification: They've had problems with people stealing this in the past, so for all intents and purposes, this is actively attempting to get out, and we can't anticipate how people will try and release it. If someone does release it, the Foundation probably wouldn't be able to tell until it causes a security breach.








